sentences: Oscar Emmanuel Peterson,  (August 15, 1925 – December 23, 2007) was a Canadian jazz pianist, virtuoso and composer.
He is considered one of history's great jazz pianists, and played thousands of concerts worldwide in a career lasting more than 60 years.
